17 or in accordance with Code Section 45-18-5 providing for the inclusion of members of
18 the local board of education and their spouses and dependents within any health insurance
19 plan or plans established under Article 1 of Chapter 18 of Title 45. It shall be the duty
20 of the board to make the employer contributions required for the operation of such plan
21 or plans. Except as provided in paragraph (3) of this subsection, a board providing such
22 insurance shall pay no greater percentage of the cost of that insurance than the percentage
23 of the cost paid as an employer contribution by the state for the health insurance plan for
24 state employees pursuant to Article 1 of Chapter 18 of Title 45. The remainder of such
25 insurance costs, and all the costs of any coverage for family members, shall be paid as an
26 employee contribution by the board member. It shall be the duty of the board to deduct
27 from the salary or other remuneration of qualified members or otherwise collect such
28 payment from the qualified members or dependents."
29 SECTION 2.
30 Said chapter is further amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
31 "20-2-219.1.
32 (a) Beginning July 1, 2025, and continuing thereafter, each local school system shall, upon
33 hiring a new employee, provide such new employee the following:
34 (1) Notice of whether:
35 (A) Social security taxes will be withheld from his or her pay;
36 (B) He or she is eligible to be included in a plan with coverage for the benefits of Title
37 II of the Social Security Act; and
38 (C) He or she is eligible to be included in any other pension or retirement plan; and
39 (2) If he or she is eligible to be included in one or more plans provided for in
40 subparagraph (B) or (C) of paragraph (1) of this subsection, information regarding such
41 plan or plans.
